The R² gap between Model A and Model B quantifies how much runtime variance requires runtime-observable signals to explain, but does not indicate whether that gap arises from memory bandwidth constraints or compute limitations. The roofline model addresses the gap directly by establishing theoretical peak performance bounds for each operator class relative to the T4 hardware ceilings. The achievable operational throughput of an operator is limited by the minimum between the peak computational throughput of the accelerator and the product of the accelerator's memory bandwidth and arithmetic intensity.
